Brief Description of Files:
- Entity: Base class for Patient and LabTech.
- Patient: Represents a patient with medical conditions, pending lab work, and medical history.
- LabTech: Represents a lab technician and stores processed lab work.
- LabWork: Represents a single lab test, its cost, and completion status.
- LabWorkList: Linked-list-based FIFO structure for storing LabWork pointers.
- Lab: Main manager for patients, lab techs, and lab work flow.
- Control: Interactive controller provided in starter code.
- TestControl: Tester controller provided in starter code.
- View: Menu/input boundary provided in starter code.
- Tester: Utility testing class provided in starter code.
- main.cc: Launches interactive version.
- test.cc: Launches tester version.
- Makefile: Builds both a3 and a3test.

Compilation Instructions:
- Run: make all

Execution Instructions:
- Run interactive mode with: ./a3
- Run test mode with: ./a3test

Design Notes:
- Patients own the original LabWork objects in their pending/history lists.
- When a LabTech processes lab work, the LabTech stores a copy of the completed LabWork.
- This avoids double deletion and keeps memory ownership safe.
- vector is used in Lab, which is allowed by the assignment specification.